column2: Table 3#9#3# Real Government Consumption Expenditures and Gross

column3: Government consumption expenditures and gross investment

column2: 1. Government consumption expenditures are services (such as education and national defense) produced
by government that are valued at their cost of production. Excludes government sales to other sectors
and government own-account investment (construction, software, and research and development).
2. Gross government investment consists of general government and government enterprise expenditures
for fixed assets; inventory investment is included in government consumption expenditures.
